FBIS4-46175 "jptot022__l94085" JPRS-TOT-94-022-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 19 May 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA TAJIKISTAN Secretary of Newspaper Editorial Board Assassinated Secretary of Newspaper Editorial Board Assassinated LD1905155794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1359 GMT 19 May 94 LD1905155794 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] [Text] Dushanbe May 19 TASS -- Khushvakht Khaidarsho, secretary of the editorial board of the Tajik newspaper "DZHUMKHURIAT," was shot dead early on Thursday near his home, ITAR-TASS learnt from competent sources. A criminal case has been opened over the fact of the assassination. The motives of the crime are yet to be investigated. However, criminal or political mafia, against which the reporter came out in his publications, are not ruled out. A wave of assassinations has swept the republic recently. Olim Abulov, an employee of the National Broadcasting Company, was riddled dead from a machine gun on May 17. Vladimir Nirma, head of the joint U.S.-Tajik enterprise "Interfer," was also shot dead from a machine gun on May 18.
